caption: These bright fun colors surely brings back summer vibes! We are so happy that restaurants are back open. Food was delicious!! Pasta and bread are usually heavy feats for me, but everything was so perfectly portioned! Would definitely recommend if you’re into lighter flavors and fruity cocktails.

First time here and Oh goodness! The drinks are good, the stuffed cabbage was too but the shrimp and squid ink spaghetti OH BOY that was so good it made my soul smile 😊 the hospitality was great as well! Good food and atmosphere i will be dining again and telling my family and friends about this place

This softly lit restaurant transports you out of cold, grey Baltimore to a quaint yet chic restaurant you just happened to find yourself in while wandering the streets of a small town in Italy. Now I'm sure this sounds cheesy, but the stepping through Orto's doors really made me feel like I was transported out of the US (or at least out of Maryland). Maybe its the lack of traveling I have done due to the pandemic, or maybe its just a magical place... I guess you'll have to see for yourself!  My partner and I started dinner off with the arancini. These perfectly fried risotto balls were complex in flavor, and yet light at the same time. The fennel sauce and tomatoes that were paired with it created a light and cleansing element which made this risotto dish very balanced.  For my main course, I had the Charred Broccolini Orecchiette. The charred broccolini made this dish smoky while the poached golden raisins delivered surprising pops of sweetness to this already clever dish. I have to say this tops my list of all time favorite pasta dishes!  Unfortunately, we were not able to save room for dessert! Next time I go to Orto, I will be ordering the Lemon Pistachio Cake though. I cannot even try and recall the number of them I watched come out of the kitchen.  Overall this restaurant gets a 5/5. The food was unbeatable, the ambiance was magical, the music was always on point, and the service was stellar! Some may say it is pricey, but you can taste the quality in the ingredients that they use. Although it is not a place I can afford to each at often, I will be coming back as soon as I can!
Excellent takeout operation. Highly recommend the parm dinner and boozy jello shots. Can't wait to visit again in person!

Dinner last night at Orto was phenomenal (as usual).  I have tried just about everything on the menu, but settled on starting with the brussels sprouts, then venturing to the shrimp w/ squid ink torchetto, and finally the seared scallops.  Top it off with a tasty rye Manhattan and I couldn't have asked for a better dining experience in the crazy year that 2020 has been.  Can't wait to go back again and again...
Great Italian food..
Love the new pasta club! Delicious and very easy to make at home. The BEST customer service.

Huge fan of orto. Tasty affordable wines. Delicious vegetarian and pescatarian items. Can get drafty when very cold outside. UPDATE: Incredibly generous when ordering software error led to food delays. Delivered it to my house for free, included wine and extra desserts on this order, and the next one!
Excellent service and food
Good food with a great outdoor seating. Must visit in Baltimore
Orto has incredibly delicious food and a great personable staff! Also locally owned and operated so support small business and go to Orto!
Great spot for date night. Patio seating for COVID is super cute.

I have eaten at Orto a handful of times now. Each time I think it can’t get any better it does. Elan and his staff absolutely live up to their best of Baltimore titles and then some. The space is gorgeous, out door dining is perfect, service is knowledgeable and flawless, and the food is out of the world. Don’t sleep on this place.

This place was fantastic! I obly say that cause i cant describe with words how many times i just about dropped my fork due to how great every plate of food was. Normally I'd be a little concerned about a place like this putting a hurtin on my wallet but by the end of meal it was worth it. Will certainly be going back soon!

First dinner out in 6.5 months and Orto did not disappoint. They particularly excelled in the appetizers (roasted corn arancini, bruschetta) and desserts (blueberry cheesecake, peach melba). Entrees were also quite good. Very attentive service. Our waiter helped us to select the perfect wine. Offering sidewalk dining (pros: social distancing, cons: flies, cigarette smoke).
Very good service. Excellent selection of cocktails (they even have a separate Spritz specific list). Loved the Burrata antipasto and the cavatelli with lamb ragù.
Hands down the best experience in Baltimore. Secret- order takeout and you can usual get the worlds best chicken parm.
This place was amazing!! Food and service was spectacular! Steak dinner green sauce was on point!
Exceptional food. We will bring out the China next time, as the food deserves it. Tom

This was only my second time here and it did not disappoint! They now have lovely outside seating since Baltimore City indoor dining was closed (COVID) when we went. Highly recommend making a reservation if you can plan ahead!
Excellent service and most importantly amazing food. THE LAMB BOLOGNESE CAVATELLI IS AMAZING!!!! Also solid desserts - had an amazing coconut cream pie
First, their pasta has always been amazing.  We again went tonight and it was amazing. Carbonara  was excellent and the mains were awesome. Great staff, great food, just awesome. Thanks!
Great atmosphere, food and service!
One of the best restaurants I have ever been to. I haven’t eaten something here that I haven’t liked.

I had made reservations for another restaurant close by but I forgot it was next week. This other restaurant recommended Orto. We shared an appetizer and had 2 of their pastas. The portions were good size and just right and everything was great. We had a wonderful server who explained in detail how our appetizer and pastas were made. Great food, service and location. Same block as the Charles Theater.

My friend and I returned to Orto again and enjoyed a wonderful feast. We decided to order multiple small plates and it was so delicious. Our dinner included marinated olives, eggplant with burrata, kale and fried sunchoke salad, mussels, shaved prosciutto, the must have chicken liver mousse and pappardelle & wild mushrooms. The service was perfect. The restaurant is delightfully decorated. We had a wonderful evening. If I could give 10 stars, I would.

We picked up a Sunday roast meal during quarantine. My husband said it was the best takeout he'd ever had. The chicken was cooked perfectly, the spring veggies and salad were super fresh, the potato puree was insanely good and dessert was delicious (it lasted about 4 days it was such a generous portion). Highly recommended and great way to support a local business!
Excellent food, knowledgeable and friendly service.  Highly recommend!
We didn't feel that the product met the price point.
Food was amazing service was on top and the wine was to die for

A consistent great experience all around. Food is always delicious, service is professional and yet relaxed. Atmosphere is a cool vibe - intimate. As a New Yorker the bar is always high for us, Porto meets that bar.
Amazing fresh pastas // wonderful menu, and really good drinks
Sooo good. Best Italian in Baltimore.

I've decided this is a poser restaurant. At bottom, it's just not that good. Recent sea bass: heartbreakingly bland. Recent pasta: ok. Recent pasta for my wife: awful. Some solid drinks (River Po!).  Staff is pretty solid too. But this place is no Bottega or Collette. Better Italian is down Charles Street.

Had a lovely dinner at Orto with friends. The space is small, but the atmosphere is vibrant. There is a small parking lot directly across the street from the entrance which accepts cash payment only. You can also try for street parking out front, but need luck on your side. We started with the burrata and it was light and tasty, but it didn’t wow me. The Orto Caesar should not be understated. It’s a good option to get started with if you plan on having dessert. I ordered a pasta dish featuring lasagna-type noodles with curls on the ends and different kinds of mushrooms, but I found the dish to be a bit dry and it would have benefited from more sauce or cheese or both. The cheesecake was very rich and tasty, but the Zeppole won my heart, for sure!! The red wine selection was also impressive and hit the mark. I will try the Bronzino on the menu next time, which cake recommended by our server and is a personal favorite.
Sorry but the service was atrocious. We didnt get our drinks for 30 minutes. The main course took 45 minutes and our appetizer was brought after a main plate. What on earth happened?

My wife and I went on a Monday night, and it was packed. We had a reservation and was promptly seated. Our waiter was consistently attentive and did a good job. Our mussels were tasty. The pasta dishes we had were out of this world. I would highly recommend this restaurant and will be personally going back for a second visit.
Delicious, flavorful food. I went on New Year's Eve and can't wait to go back.

Got there at sat at the bar waiting for our table. Our burratta took 25 minutes. Once at our table, it took 15 minutes to be acknowledged. I asked for coffee and it didn’t come until after our dinner plates were there. It was super loud and a bad experience. Will not return
Fantastic food and service. Highly recommend for any dinner or romantic evening.
Orto definitely deserves it's best new restaurant in the city rating.  I keep coming back for happy hour!!!

Enjoyed Collette, Orto's predecessor in this space on Charles Street, next to the Charles Theater. The space is still charming. The service was courteous. Unfortunately, the food was far from great. The mushroom appetizer tasted as if it came from a bottle off the shelf of a grocery store. The olives were over seasoned with tarragon (?), tasting of anise more than olives. The eggplant with burrata - the eggplant was burnt to a crisp. The pasta dish was dry, as if it had been sitting around, then reheated under a salamander. I won't be going back.

Excellent food and cocktails. Welcoming atmosphere. Walked in after a bad food experience and bartender Nick had great energy and was very knowledgeable about the menu. The ribs and duck rags pasta are super good and the goat cheese cheesecake amazing. Really soft and rich. Nick created some cocktails based on preference and they were really really good. Will be back again!!
Fun, happy atmosphere, attentive servers and good food and drinks!!👍
If you're a foodie you'll love it!

One of the best meals I’ve had in Baltimore, ever. Our server was attentive, knowledgeable, and fun. He explained everything as well as ever could have been expected. Our courses came out perfectly cooked and seasoned. The wine pairing was great. The atmosphere was casual but sophisticated. This is the 3rd meal I’ve had here and it has never disappointed. AAA+++
From the charred beet salad to the unique handmade pastas to the in-house gelato and finishing up with a supreme digestif selection, this is the new spot for a night out in Station North.
Over the top service and great food.
Food was excellent, but what made. Difference was the attentiveness of the staff.

Extremely tasty offerings with portion size and pricing that left me hungry for more. Had to ask for bread (extremely tasty also) twice so as to not be seen licking the plates in public. Definitely will visit again!

Orto is still relatively new to the neighborhood but I hope it sticks around for a while. The menu is relatively simple, but massively delicious. The ambiance and decor are spot on, the lighting is low and romantic. The art and furniture have a certain maturity. The prices are reasonable but not cheap, and they wouldn't be for this type of experience, making it a reasonable value. The food is delicious and well presented. The portions are solid and leave just enough space for dessert. They have an awesome snack menu that includes olives and almonds, two of my favorites. The desserts are well worth it, too. The area is very lively on a Saturday night, outdoor seating allowing you to enjoy the energy of the street. If you're looking for a trendy Italian dining experience, Orto will not disappoint. I reccomend the grilled skirt steak.  Traveler and Adventurer - IG @brian.dent

My favorite restaurant! Wr drive from PA to dine at Orto. The food is fabulous! I have enjoyed everything I have eaten there, but especially recommend the bronzino. I cannot say enough about the incredible service and knowledgeable servers! (Shout out to Virginia! ❤)
This isnmy favorite place in all of baltimore! The whole staff is incredibly helpful and nice, and the chef and owner are wonderful!
Food was tasty and restaurant has a nice atmosphere

They recently won best new restaurant and it's easy to see why. Great food and service. The atmosphere is something you would see in any major city but still feels familiar. The staff was friendly and knowledgeable. I visited on restaurant week and enjoyed all the option.
Baltimore Restaurant week menu was on point. Great spot. Must try.

This is one of our favorite places to visit in the city - the food and drinks are top notch, the ambiance is relaxed, and the staff are all very friendly and good at what they do. We went tonight with our 3 week old baby on our first dinner out with him, and the staff were incredibly helpful and accommodating. They immediately understood that we were probably on a time budget with the tiny baby and so were very attentive and brought our food quickly. It was a great experience, and they are well deserving of all the praise they get!

Great ambiance for- date night, work dinner, solo dining etc. While there are always a good amount of people during peak hours, it is not noisy. The music is set somewhere between casual dining & chill vibe tunes; allowing customers to dine, read, and/or engage in conversation , which is a big plus for me! The menu is fairly priced and I have enjoyed several of the menu items. I highly recommend their happy hour menu and make note of the highly competent,attentive, and welcoming staff.

Orto has been on my list since it opened and when I finally got the opportunity to check it out, I was not disappointed. I had a delicious balsamic mushroom appetizer followed by the Maryland-inspired squid ink spaghetti with crab and a Negroni cocktail that was out of this world. The blend of classic and contemporary flavors delivered in a rather unique fashion definitely make this place worth a visit!

A very exceptional experience in dining.  I found the service great. The wait person was very knowledgeable in explaining the various dishes..i found this very helpful with making my decision as to what to order. The food was very good..i would certainly recommend ORTO..being from NYC  I found that the restaurant was comparable to many fine places in the city. Having enjoyed the meal and the desert..in I will certainly go back

This is my favorite restaurant in Baltimore, but really a favorite period.  I love everything about the place.  Nice vibe in the space, consistently excellent food even when Stephano is not there.  Each time I try something new, I am pleasantly surprised.  I am an objectively critical foodie so this is no easy pass!  Orto really does an especially beautiful job with pasta and vegetables.  Just a great place.
Just tried their new Sunday brunch, and we were blown away! We went with the American Breakfast, as well as the “Sunday’s at Elan’s” dish. I can’t recommend this place enough.
Great food and atmosphere. The octopus and the scallops are great. From desserts the olive oil ice cream is great to try.

Very good bar and happy hour menu here. If you like amaro liqueurs this is one of the better places in Baltimore. The food is very well prepared and not served in excessively large portions. Plus it's very healthy.
Been a couple of times, wow. Food so good, drinks as well. Everything was my favorite. Only ding is that the kitchen could use a little better pacing, not fond of multiple courses showing up at once.

Went Saturday night, the place was hopping.  The service was very good and the owner and chef were walking around throughout the night to check on things which I like to see.  Having been here at the opening a few months ago, they have truly come a long way!  The food was amazing! We had the burrata, some small plates, 3 pastas, all different yet equally delicious, the spring pea agnolotti my favorite. The suckling pig, branzino and chicken Milanese were also perfect though the chicken was a little salty, an easy fix.  The desserts were also really great, especially the hazelnut torte and homemade ice creams and sorbet.  This could be vying for the top of Italian restaurants in Baltimore!
Went to Orto for Mother's Day and it did not disappoint.  We liked everything and will be back for a nice meal.

I came for dinner and drinks and hesitated to even leave a review as the staff was friendly, and the experience was mostly fine. However, there was a fairly serious service mistake (which staff attempted to rectify with complimentary desert) and the food was tasty but a bit overpriced and high-minded in concept but not in execution. Cocktails are good, appetizers are well portioned and tasty, but menu descriptions are inexact and misleading. It seems like a mostly passable mixed bag.
It was nice
Went to Orto with a friend and the ambiance was serene and the food was divine. They held true to their mission of delicious, fresh, ingredients, prepared simply. Thanks Elan & Stefano!
The food was excellent and of high quality
Nice space, great food, decent prices.

I accidentally discovered this gem on a night out with friends, even though we had originally planned on having dinner at another restaurant a few doors down. None of us knew what to expect because this was our first time at Orto. However, as enthusiasts of Italian food, we were so pleased with our choices! Between the three of us, we ordered the butternut squash agnolotti, pomodoro e ravioli, and rigatoni 'alla norma, all of which were divine! Our only complaint was that the portions were small, but we made sure to savor every bite. Afterwards, we ordered coffee and a hazelnut crème brûlée, which were also exquisite. The service and ambiance of the restaurant were also wonderful.  This restaurant was a bit out of my usual price range, but it was so worth it! I can't wait to come back soon, although I think that I would struggle to choose between all the amazing options!

Great food with a cool intimate setting and vibe for Italian food. This place is a “drive out of your way” worthy new place. Loved the interesting appetizers (conserves) olives with preserved lemon and marinated mushroom also the burata flatbread was so good we ordered two, it was super fresh and had this really tasty sweat onion jam. Some really nice pastas and the best was an agnolotti butternut squash stuffed pasta with Madeira and sage. Lastly we all agreed that the dessert was the best we have ever had at an Italian restaurant... the Italian donuts (zeppelini) and the most wonderful blood orange brown butter tart made us wish we had ordered a second round to have the next day! Definitely will be back, great addition to the neighborhood!

I went to Orto thinking it was still Bottega, which used to occupy the same space. The decor was the same and so was most of the staff, which were already perfect and I’m glad they didn’t change! The service was outstanding and I was thrilled I could still get the magical blood orange tart I had loved at Bottega. Everything we ordered was delicious, but I felt that the portion size was a little small for the price. It’s hard not to draw comparisons to Bottega since so much is the same, and while we had a lovely meal and spent $125 on it, we left a bit hungry. Nevertheless, the pasta is the best I’ve had, and I’m sure I’ll be back!
Thank you, thank you, thank you for the best meal I’ve had in Bmore in as long as I can remember. Everything we tasted was as good or as better as the next.
Best food in the 'station north' area!  Relaxed vibe, quality eats!!!
username: D I V E R S I F O R M

caption: Excellent food, service and ambiance!  We will definitely be coming back.
Food = Amazing. Service even better. Elan made us feel like family!
Superb food. Sublime atmosphere.

From start to finish, our meal was perfect. From the Boquerones to the Pricipale ...Orto highlights the lighter side of Italian Cuisine. The Anchovies were a delicate perfection to start our meal .. the chicken liver mousse was some of the best I’ve had, home-made pastas are melt in your mouth delicious, tender chicken Milanese, and do not pass up that opportunity for dessert - such as flourless chocolate cake w/homemade Chestnut ice cream or the beet sorbetto. Plan ahead with a reservation - the space is small so seating is limited.

Went with a good friend to try out this brand new place. Everything was extremely flavorful, well presented, & generously proportioned. Service was spot on. The chicken liver mousse crostino is TO DIE FOR!
